name: Kepler-186
commentary:
When discovered in April 2014, Kepler 186f was the first Earth sized planet known to orbit in the habitable zone around its host star.

Host Star: Kepler 186

Host Star Type: Red Dwarf - M Type Main Sequence

Constellation: Cygnus

Distance from Earth: 500 light years

Mass: Unknown, between 0.5 to 2 times that of Earth depending on composition

Diameter: Around 8,800 miles (14,300 km)

Distance from host star:  60 million km

Orbital Period: 130 Earth days

Temperature: Unknown

name: Kepler-452
commentary:
Kepler 452b, discovered in 2015, is considered the most Earth like planet yet discovered due to its size, location in its system and the type of star it orbits.

Host Star: Kepler 452

Host Star Type: Main Sequence - G Class (Yellow Dwarf)

Constellation: Cygnus

Distance from Earth: 1,400 light years

Mass: Unknown, possibly around 4 to 5 times that of Earth.

Diameter: Around 12,800 miles (21,000 km)

Distance from host star: 98 million miles (158 million km)

Orbital Period: 385 Earth days

Surface Temperature: -
